Package models

Class User

java.lang.Object
models.User
Direct Known Subclasses:
CareerCenterStaff, CompanyRepresentative, Student
public class User extends Object
Represents an User object. A User will contain:
  1. User ID
  2. Name
  3. Password
  4. Email
  5. Type of User

A User object can be one of the types below:
  1. User
  2. Student
  3. Career Center Staff
  4. Company Representative
Other than the default type (User), every other User type will also include their own specific fields.

ALL Users will have access to basic user management features, including login, logout and change password.

    Nested Classes
    Modifier and Type
    Class
    Description
    static enum 
    User.TypesOfUser
    Enum that contains different user account types - User, Student, CareerCenterStaff, CompanyRepresentative
    User objects of type "Student" and "Career Center Staff" are automatically assigned their respective types from the sample excel file.

    The default type "User" is initiated first, as in the case of "Company Representative" they must be approved by a user
    that is a "Career Center Staffs" type first, before officially becoming a "Company Representative".

    • setPassword

      public String setPassword(String oldPass, Scanner sc)
      Change user's password

      Checks if user's new password has:
      • At least 8 characters
      • At least 1 Uppercase letter
      • At least 1 Digit
      • At least 1 Special Character
      Parameters:
      oldPass - current password to validate against
      sc - Scanner instance to read new password from
      Returns:
      the new password if changed, empty string if cancelled

    • isValidPassword

      public static boolean isValidPassword(String password)
      Helper function for setPassword() to validate new password entered.
      Parameters:
      password - Takes in user's old password to enable password change.
      1. true with system message: "Valid new password"
      2. false with system message: "Invalid new password" and returns false
      Returns:
      boolean value indicating if new password is valid
